{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, a smaller group of students deliberately avoided using AI assistance.",
    "Recent study conducted by Stojanov et al. (2024) also explores profiles based on self-reported reliance level of students while interacting with ChatGPT.",
    "They identify five distinct profiles of reliance as \"versatile low reliers\", \"knowledge seekers\", \"pro-active learners\", \"task-delegators\", and \"all-rounders\".",
    "\"Versatile low reliers\" have the lowest self-reported reliance; \"knowledge seekers\" uses AI for content acquisition, information retrieval, and summarization; \"pro-active learners\" get help from ChatGPT as obtaining feedback, planning, and quizzing; \"task-delegators\" relied on ChatGPT for completing assignments; and \"all-rounders\" has highest selfreported reliance on ChatGPT (Stojanov et al., 2024).",
    "Both studies highlight a spectrum of reliance on ChatGPT, from minimal (AI-Independent Coders and \"versatile low reliers\") to high (AI-Reliant Code Generators and \"task-delegators\")."
  ]
}